Package edu.ncsu.csc216.wolf_scheduler.scheduler

Class WolfScheduler

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.ncsu.csc216.wolf_scheduler.scheduler.WolfScheduler
  • public class WolfScheduler
extends java.lang.Object
    WolfScheduler reads in and stores as a list all of the Course records stored in a file Additionally, WolfScheduler creates a schedule for the current user (a student) and provides functionality for naming the schedule, adding a Course to the schedule, removing a Course from the schedule, resetting the schedule.
    Author:
    symone

    • Method Detail

      • getCourseCatalog

        public java.lang.String[][] getCourseCatalog()
        Returns a 2D String array of the catalog used in the GUI to create the table of course catalog information. There is a row for each Course and three columns for name, section, and title. If there are no Courses in the catalog, an empty 2D String array is returned.
        Returns:
        catalogArray a 2D String array of the catalog

      • getScheduledActivities

        public java.lang.String[][] getScheduledActivities()
        Returns a 2D String array of the schedule. This array is used in the GUI to create the table of course catalog information. There is a row for each Course and four columns for name, section, and title. If there are no Courses in the schedule, an empty 2D String array is returned.
        Returns:
        scheduleArray 2D array of the schedule

      • getFullScheduledActivities

        public java.lang.String[][] getFullScheduledActivities()
        Returns a 2D String array of the schedule with all information. This array is used in the GUI to create the table of course catalog information. There is a row for each Course and seven columns for name, section, title, credits, instructorId, and the meeting days string. If there are no Courses in the schedule, an empty 2D String array is returned.
        Returns:
        fullScheduleArray full schedule with all Course information.

        Parameters:

        Returns:
        Course found in catalog, else returns null.

      • addCourseToSchedule

        public boolean addCourseToSchedule​(java.lang.String name,
                                   java.lang.String section)
                            throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        Returns true if the given Course (represented by the name and section) meets the following criteria: the course exists in the catalog and the course is successfully added to the student’s schedule. If the Course is not in the catalog, it cannot be added to the schedule and the method returns false.
        Parameters:
        name - name of the Course
        section - section of the Course
        Returns:
        true if the Course can be added to the schedule else returns false.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if name of course matches.

      • addEventToSchedule

        public void addEventToSchedule​(java.lang.String eventTitle,
                               java.lang.String eventMeetingDays,
                               int eventStartTime,
                               int eventEndTime,
                               java.lang.String eventDetails)
                        throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        If the new Event is a duplicate of an existing Event in the schedule, an IllegalArgumentException should be thrown with the message “You have already created an event called [event title]”.
        Parameters:
        eventTitle - title of the Event to be added
        eventMeetingDays - meeting days of the Event to be added
        eventStartTime - start time of the Event to be added.
        eventEndTime - end time of the Event to be added.
        eventDetails - details of the Event to be added.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if event is already in schedule

      • removeActivityFromSchedule

        public boolean removeActivityFromSchedule​(int idx)
        Returns true if the given Course (represented by the name and section) can be removed from the student’s schedule. The Course is then removed. The method returns false if the Course isn’t in the schedule.
        Parameters:
        idx - index of the Activity to be removed from schedule.
        Returns:
        false if the course can be removed, else returns true.
